{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"15e6337c-80a2-4b3f-95d9-53ad2ab37980","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_pgTUZbIEE3jFOeBvIiUKvb","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Providing K8s crash dump config"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"467517e5-e675-40d0-865d-29d7b25bfa43","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. I need to provide:\n\n1. The environment variables needed to configure .NET to use createdump for automatic crash dump collection\n2. The Kubernetes pod spec changes needed (volume mounts for dump storage, environment variables, etc.)\n\nFor .NET NativeAOT crash dump collection, the key environment variables are:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - enables crash dumps\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` - dump type (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` - path/pattern for dump files\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics` - enable diagnostics for createdump itself\n\nThe `DOTNET_` prefix is the current standard (replacing the older `COMPlus_` prefix). For NativeAOT specifically, I need to point to the createdump executable explicitly since it's not bundled by default, and the runtime will invoke it when a crash occurs.\n\nFor the pod spec, I'm setting up the environment variables like `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1`, `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4`, and `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` to specify where dumps go, plus `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` to locate the createdump tool. I'll also need to configure a volume for dump storage and likely add the `SYS_PTRACE` capability so createdump can attach to the process.","outputTokens":636,"requestId":"CB01:2C00FF:1FA8CA7:22EBBB2:6A0529C8"},"id":"b4246f1a-bd7b-4654-9d99-4ddcb2f37c2e","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:48:06.019Z","parentId":"e34d944f-1355-4361-9ae7-f41aeeb587f1"}
