{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fd2a33f7-1c04-4337-9599-d59fea0068ca","content":"Here's what you need for automatic crash dump collection with NativeAOT .NET 11:\n\n**Environment variables** (on your container):\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"            # 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/dumps/core.%p.%t\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n```\n\n**Pod spec changes:**\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  shareProcessNamespace: true   # needed if using sidecars to upload dumps\n  containers:\n    - name: my-app\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add: [\"SYS_PTRACE\"]   # required for createdump to attach\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: dumps\n          mountPath: /dumps\n      # ... env vars above ...\n  volumes:\n    - name: dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi          # adjust based on expected dump size\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`SYS_PTRACE`** is required — `createdump` uses `ptrace` to snapshot the process.\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** tells the NativeAOT runtime where to find `createdump` (it's not bundled in NativeAOT builds).\n- **Dump type 4 (Full)** gives the most debugging info but produces large files; use type 1 (Mini) if storage is tight.\n- Replace `emptyDir` with a PVC if you need dumps to survive pod restarts.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"467517e5-e675-40d0-865d-29d7b25bfa43","outputTokens":450,"requestId":"CB01:2C00FF:1FAC2DF:22EF861:6A0529D5"},"id":"b6903342-940d-4cd2-a5e8-492ebac807ce","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:48:15.651Z","parentId":"d9cf61cb-9b2a-4809-ab5c-bd1969eae3ea"}
